A $19.4 million plan to reduce pollution and restore bay grasses and oyster habitat to the Corsica River was announced by Maryland Governor Robert L. Ehrlich Jr. Tuesday as a ``blueprint'' for saving the Chesapeake Bay.
Washington Post Staff Writer 

Restoring the Chesapeake Bay's dwindling oyster beds would accelerate efforts to clean the bay's waters, reducing nitrogen and algae problems and fostering the growth of underwater plant life, Maryland researchers said Friday.
